According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Mining Equipment Market was valued at USD 129.9 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 148.2 billion by 2032, growing at a CAGR of 1.9% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady expansion as mining companies worldwide increase investments in advanced equipment to improve productivity, operational efficiency, worker safety, and environmental sustainability. Rising global demand for minerals and metals, fueled by infrastructure development, renewable energy projects, electric vehicle production, and industrial manufacturing, continues to support long-term demand for modern mining equipment. Simultaneously, technological advancements such as automation, artificial intelligence (AI), telematics, Internet of Things (IoT), and electrification are transforming mining operations, enabling companies to optimize resource utilization while reducing operational costs and emissions.
